{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context / Problem\nDiscovered while closing tickets this session. The completion-verification gate's LLM verifier (rebar verify-completion / the close-gate _completion_precheck) returns NON-DETERMINISTIC verdicts for IDENTICAL inputs — same ticket, same code at HEAD, same acceptance criteria, same ticket comments — within minutes and with no changes between runs.\n\n## Evidence (ticket ad9f-45f1-339f-4346, code at origin/main HEAD, unchanged between runs)\n- `rebar verify-completion ad9f --output json` standalone -> verdict PASS, 0 findings.\n- `rebar transition ad9f in_progress closed` (same gate, moments later) -> \"completion verification FAILED — 2 unmet criteria; not closing\".\n- Immediate retry `rebar transition ad9f in_progress closed` -> PASS, ticket closed.\nThree runs, three effectively different outcomes (PASS / FAIL-2 / PASS) with no intervening change.\n\n## Impact\n- The close gate is unreliable in BOTH directions: it can spuriously BLOCK a legitimately-complete ticket (wasting an LLM run and forcing retries) and — the more dangerous direction — spuriously PASS a genuinely-incomplete ticket on a lucky run. A gate whose verdict flips on identical input cannot be trusted to certify completion.\n- Interacts badly with the completion close mechanics (see 4de6): flaky FAILs during a close are expensive (billed LLM) and confusing; flaky PASSes undermine the whole attestation.\n\n## Root-cause hypothesis\nLLM sampling non-determinism: the verifier runs the model without pinned/deterministic decoding (temperature/seed) and/or without multi-sample aggregation, so per-run sampling variance flips borderline criteria between upheld/unmet. Model: pydantic_ai/claude-* per config.\n\n## Suggested fixes\n- Pin decoding for the verifier (temperature 0 and/or a fixed seed where the provider supports it) so identical inputs are reproducible.\n- Multi-sample majority/quorum vote per criterion with a declared threshold (the plan-review gate already uses a multi-pass verify structure; mirror it).\n- Distinguish a genuine FAIL from a flaky one: on a non-PASS close, allow a bounded retry/quorum before failing closed, and surface a 'low-confidence / non-reproducible' signal rather than a hard FAIL.\n- Add a determinism regression check (run the verifier N times on a fixed fixture; require identical verdicts).\n\n## Relation to our changes\nUNRELATED to the 790c/80af/ad9f/4de6 code changes — this is the LLM-verifier layer (verify_completion), not the git-tree/ref plumbing those touched.\n\n## Possibly related (same session / same subsystem)\n- review-code silent-empty output when invoked non-interactively/backgrounded (exits 0 with an empty result — indistinguishable from a clean 0-findings pass). (From the 4de6 report.)\n- PlanReviewGenerationChanged raised with IDENTICAL before==after generation hashes; a blind re-run signs. Also a currency/consistency check that fails against itself.\n\n## Scope of THIS ticket (agreed) + Acceptance Criteria\nResolve e458 with two concrete, testable changes; the residual multi-sample quorum / deeper determinism hardening is a separate follow-up (see idea 4217 family).\n- [ ] The COMPLETION_VERDICT sidecar payload (BOTH the PASS `completion_verifier_pass_v1` and FAIL `completion_verifier_fail_v1` schemas, via build_payload) records `verified_at_sha` (the immutable commit the verifier ran against; None in local mode) and `trace_id` (the model-run id), so two sidecars can be compared for input-identity from stored data alone — verified by a unit test on build_payload for both PASS and FAIL.\n- [ ] The completion verifier pins model sampling temperature to 0 (greedy) by default — cfg.temperature is set to 0.0 in _verify_completion_inner UNLESS the operator explicitly set REBAR_LLM_TEMPERATURE (an explicit value wins), mirroring the model/step-floor tuning already there and the plan-review Pass-2 verifier's greedy pin — verified by a test that the tuned cfg.temperature is 0.0 by default and preserves an explicit non-None value.\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green.\nNote: temperature 0 is a MITIGATION (reduces sampling variance), not a proof of determinism; combined with the recorded verified_at_sha it makes any residual drift observable (identical input, identical decoding) rather than ambiguous."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784843180599434001,"uuid":"ea9df3d7-b089-45af-9f9b-8e797a8e3e54"}